ec up to 213K.  Average IO size is the same as 4.3-rc1.<br /><br />Ok, so at least for you, part of the problem really ends up being that<br />there's a mix of the "synchronous" unplugging (by the actual explicit<br />"blk_finish_plug(&amp;plug);") and the writeback that is handed off to<br />kblockd_workqueue.<br /><br />I'm not seeing why that should be an issue. Sure, there's some CPU<br />overhead to context switching, but I don't see that it should be that<br />big of a deal.<br /><br />I wonder if there is something more serious wrong with the kblockd_workqueue.<br /><br />                    Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
